Everything we had was fabulous, including the pizza Italia, the salmon, the calimari, and the risotto. My dad called the calimari "the best I've ever had".  The desserts we ordered were also excellent: panna cotta (cream and gelatin), Italian cheesecake (a little less sweet and much lighter than what in used to), tortufa (vanilla and chocolate ice cream in a chocolate shell with a cherry in the middle)  And the prices aren't nearly as expensive as you might expect for the quality of food.  The dining room is a bit on the small size, but the staff was friendly and the atmosphere was cozy.

Yesterday was our first visit to this restaurant. We brought our out of town relatives who had eaten here before and had given the place a high recommendation. The place lived up and more than surpassed our expectations. There's  a nice ambiance, great service and the quality of the food is excellent. We came in on a cold and rainy afternoon to be warmed by the brick oven inside the place. From the flat bread they welcomed us with to the great desserts we enjoyed, we all had great meals. I had a delicious calamari over an arugula salad that I can't wait to try again. My wife ordered a delicious lasagna. This restaurant will definitely see us back soon and often.
